sentences: Jeffrey Foucault (born January 26, 1976) is an American songwriter and record producer from  Whitewater, Wisconsin, United States, whose work marries the influence of American country, blues, rock 'n' roll, and folk music.
Foucault has toured extensively in the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom and Europe since 2001, in both full-band and solo appearances.
Since 2013 he has performed as a duo with drummer Billy Conway (Morphine, Treat Her Right).
Foucault's solo releases were previously issued by western Massachusetts-based independent label Signature Sounds, including Stripping Cane (2004), Ghost Repeater (2006) and Horse Latitudes (2011).
